Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.59,0:00:02.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A journey of a thousand miles \Nstarts with the first step!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.32,0:00:04.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Solve 1,000 mysteries and enter a new world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.49,0:00:06.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The legendary case that took \Nplace on a remote island!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.36,0:00:08.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is the mystery behind \Nthe cursed piano and melody?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.84,0:00:10.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.51,0:00:12.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.17,0:00:14.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.21,0:00:38.72,DCNote,NOTE,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&HD2D3D1&\c&H6E6E6E&\b1\an8}During the next full moon\Nonce again on Moonshade Island\Nthe shadows will begin to vanish\N\NPlease investigate the case\N\NAso Keiji
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.01,0:02:02.01,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(356,1)}The Moonlight Sonata Murder \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.57,0:02:00.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Moonlight Sonata Murder, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.18,0:02:05.02,Reoccurring Signs,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(525,1)\3c&HB47375&\pos(316,318)}Moonshade Island Village Office
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.35,0:02:07.24,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There isn't anyone by that \Nname on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.24,0:02:10.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Can't you search your \Nrecords more thoroughly?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.76,0:02:14.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I have a letter from him requesting \Nmy services right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.62,0:02:19.18,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,But he's not on the island's resident list.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.18,0:02:22.60,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, I just arrived \Non this island last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.60,0:02:24.13,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.13,0:02:25.54,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.77,0:02:31.51,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,This man claims to have been hired \Nby a resident of the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.51,0:02:32.50,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Hired?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.50,0:02:36.24,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, by somebody named Aso Keiji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.24,0:02:37.96,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say Aso Keiji?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.05,0:02:45.22,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.22,0:02:45.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.25,0:02:51.22,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he passed away \Nmore than ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.25,0:02:58.23,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,It happened 12 years ago on \Nthe night of a full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.54,0:03:02.75,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,He was a famous pianist from this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.02,0:03:06.36,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,After performing a concert at \Nthe village's community center,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.36,0:03:09.62,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,he suddenly locked himself and \Nhis family inside his home
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.61,0:03:12.86,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,and set the house on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.50,0:03:15.76,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,According to the rescuers \Nwho arrived at the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.76,0:03:19.73,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,after brutally murdering his \Nwife and daughter with a knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.73,0:03:27.26,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,he played the same piece over and over \Namidst the flames like a man possessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.66,0:03:31.62,DCMain,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,It was Beethoven's "Moonlight Sonata."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.12,0:03:40.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez. What an awful prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.16,0:03:41.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It might not be a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.94,0:03:42.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.88,0:03:46.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you received \Nyour retainer fee, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.09,0:03:46.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.19,0:03:51.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And the postmark on the letter \Nis from Moonshade Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.53,0:03:52.66,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.66,0:03:59.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means someone on this island probably \Nwants you to investigate that Aso Keiji person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.91,0:04:01.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:05.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But if the man in question is dead, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.77,0:04:11.94,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try talking to the mayor who \Nwas allegedly Aso-san's friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.94,0:04:13.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.36,0:04:17.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I believe they said the mayor \Nis at the community center.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.56,0:04:17.33,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Are you listening, Kenta-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.33,0:04:19.83,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you keep yourself \Nwarm while you sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.83,0:04:20.32,DCMain,KENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.61,0:04:22.97,DCMain,KENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Doctor Narumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.97,0:04:24.52,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.52,0:04:26.48,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:27.07,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.35,0:04:30.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where the community center is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.35,0:04:36.44,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Take a right at that corner, and the \Ncommunity center is at the end of the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.44,0:04:38.81,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come here from the mainland?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.81,0:04:40.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We're from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.88,0:04:44.40,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! My family's from Tokyo, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:46.31,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.31,0:04:50.10,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But unlike Tokyo, isn't \Nthis island wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:53.37,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,The air is clear, and it's so quiet here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.90,0:04:52.43,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,Residents of Moonshade Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.43,0:04:54.31,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,in order to protect the \Nisland's fishing grounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.10,0:04:57.65,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fs30\shad0\bord3\3c&H852C21&}Community Planning with Vitality\N{\fs26}Shimuzu Masato
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.31,0:04:56.84,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,vote for me, Shimizu Masato!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.84,0:04:59.74,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,Vote for Shimizu Masato!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.90,0:05:01.15,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fs26\shad0\bord3\3c&H852C21&}Community Planning with Vitality\N{\fs22}Shimizu Masato
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.47,0:05:06.83,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Normally the island is quiet, but \Nthe mayoral election is coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.83,0:05:08.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mayoral election?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.30,0:05:09.03,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:11.54,DCMain,TOP RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs16\3c&H852C21&\b1\shad0}Community Planning with Vitality
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:11.54,DCMain,TOP LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\b1\fs16\shad0\3c&H4F24C7&}Continuing to Work with Moonshade Island\NKuroiwa Tatsuji
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:11.54,DCMain,BOTTOM LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an4\fs16\shad0\3c&HE98E3C&}Kawashima Hideo
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:11.54,DCMain,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an1\bord3\shad0\c&H852C21&\3c&HEAE2E1&}Moonshade Island \NMayoral Election\NPoster Bulletin Board
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.40,0:05:11.52,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an3}There are three candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.77,0:05:17.52,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,According to my patients, it's likely \Nthat Kawashima-san will be elected.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.52,0:05:21.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, Miss Nurse, we're not particularly \Ninterested in the mayoral election.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.07,0:05:24.65,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm Asai Narumi, a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.21,0:05:25.67,Reoccurring Signs,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(445,429)\pos(324,296)\3c&HC97989&}Asai Narumi (26)\NDoctor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:26.66,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I have a medical license.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.66,0:05:29.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. You're a doctor, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.96,0:05:34.49,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to the community center,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.49,0:05:36.89,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,you might get to meet the \Nthree men I just mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.93,0:05:41.63,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the previous \Nmayor Kameyama Isamu-san's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:45.22,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,second anniversary memorial service \Nis being held there tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:51.27,DCMain,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let Mayor Kuroiwa get \Naway with this tyranny!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:51.28,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\shad0\c&H18171A&\3c&HF0F1F1&}Get out, {\c&HF14103&\3c&HF0F1F1&}Mayor Kuroiwa!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:54.30,DCMain,VILLAGER C,0000,0000,0000,,Stop polluting our fishing grounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.30,0:05:55.66,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:59.38,Reoccurring Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(446,439)\pos(344,296)\3c&HC08089&}Kuroiwa Tatsuji (56)\NMayor of Moonshade Island
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.04,0:05:59.13,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The previous mayor's memorial \Nservice is tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.13,0:06:00.61,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}How rude of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.61,0:06:01.55,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.55,0:06:03.64,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They're so noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:04.55,Reoccurring Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(438,437)\pos(265,295)\3c&H883840&}Kuroiwa Reiko (27)\NKuroiwa's Only Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.99,0:06:04.92,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hirata.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:06.03,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:08.55,Reoccurring Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(235,296)\3c&H754446&\fad(441,433)}Hirata Kazuaki (31)\NSecretary to the Mayor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.03,0:06:07.56,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.56,0:06:10.09,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hurry up and shut up those villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:12.42,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.94,0:06:16.84,DCMain,MURASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, whoa. Are you guys okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.84,0:06:17.81,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Shuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.37,0:06:25.42,DCMain,MURASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}According to the villagers, the odds are \Nagainst your dad in the upcoming mayoral race.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.85,0:06:22.31,Reoccurring Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(445,429)\pos(340,297)\3c&HAB737A&}Murasawa Shuichi (27)\NReiko's Fiancee
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.42,0:06:26.91,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's not—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.91,0:06:28.32,DCMain,KAWASHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:33.20,DCMain,KAWASHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It seems that I have the most \Nsupport from the villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.78,0:06:33.20,Reoccurring Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,296)\3c&H873F44&\fad(444,1)}Kawashima Hideo (56)\NMayoral Election Candidate
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.15,0:06:37.30,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's because you know \Nhow to use your money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.68,0:06:41.35,DCMain,KAWASHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just copying your methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:45.22,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,There's somebody who says he'd \Nlike to meet with the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.41,0:06:47.96,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Who wants to see me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.96,0:06:52.53,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,H-He says he's a detective from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.53,0:06:53.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.88,0:06:56.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,How long are they going to make us wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.11,0:06:58.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're busy preparing \Nfor the memorial service.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:06:59.58,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.05,0:07:01.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.17,0:07:05.30,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,A piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:07.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.75,0:07:09.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.31,0:07:12.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This is a big room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.37,0:07:15.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are they going to hold a piano concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.12,0:07:20.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The ocean is right behind the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.26,0:07:23.75,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,This piano looks pretty old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.75,0:07:25.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.11,0:07:25.96,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.26,0:07:28.21,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch that piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.58,0:07:36.09,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's the cursed piano played here \Nat the concert the day Aso-san died.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.53,0:07:38.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Surely it's not cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.27,0:07:41.65,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,That incident wasn't the \Nonly thing that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.65,0:07:44.62,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Something similar happened \Nto the previous mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.08,0:07:49.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Kameyama Isamu-san, whose \Nmemorial service is being held today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.88,0:07:52.86,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It happened two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.86,0:07:57.63,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,The moon was full that night, just \Nlike the night of Aso-san's incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:08:04.23,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to pass nearby when \NI heard the sound of the piano
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.23,0:08:06.64,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,coming from the supposedly \Nempty community center.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.00,0:08:11.13,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought someone was there, so I called out \Nto them, and the sound abruptly stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:13.56,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,When I entered the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.76,0:08:18.96,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Kameyama-san was leaning \Nagainst the keys, dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.27,0:08:22.87,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of death was a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.29,0:08:27.64,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,And horrifyingly, the piece that had \Nbeen playing right up until his death
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.64,0:08:33.22,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,was the piece Aso-san played amidst \Nthe inferno, the "Moonlight Sonata."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.36,0:08:41.07,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, people started \Ncalling this the cursed piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:44.41,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,The villagers are too afraid to touch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.45,0:08:50.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing special about this piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.69,0:08:51.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.18,0:08:57.77,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, please wait outside \Nuntil the service is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.77,0:08:59.71,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.71,0:09:00.68,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Narumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.75,0:09:03.49,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Were you able to meet with the mayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:05.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.82,0:09:07.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you here for the service, Narumi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.82,0:09:08.70,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.14,0:09:14.16,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kameyama-san's was the first body I \Nexamined after coming to the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:16.72,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I could at least \Nlight some incense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.22,0:09:21.32,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, right. This is one of the mayoral \Ncandidates I mentioned earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.83,0:09:24.29,Reoccurring Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(439,436)\pos(416,297)\3c&HB36166&}Shimizu Masato (49)\NMayoral Election Candidate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.67,0:09:24.28,DCMain,SHIMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Nice to meet you. I'm Shimizu Masato.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.58,0:09:25.77,DCMain,SHIMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,A pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.01,0:09:39.55,Reoccurring Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(441,1)\pos(214,295)\3c&H883F43&}Nishimoto Ken (55)\NUnemployed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.91,0:09:44.95,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.80,0:09:49.66,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,You hired a detective to \Ninvestigate me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.96,0:09:52.43,DCMain,KAWASHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.43,0:09:54.18,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you running away from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:09:57.16,DCMain,KAWASHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.11,0:10:04.37,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.37,0:10:10.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly no one's used that piano \Nin years, but it was in tune.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.26,0:10:13.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's probably been tuning it in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.21,0:10:19.18,DCNote,NOTE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs20\c&H6E6E6E&\3c&HF0F1F1&\fad(695,187)\b1}During the next full moon\Nonce again on Moonshade Island\Nthe shadows will begin to vanish\N\NPlease investigate the case\N\NAso Keiji
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:17.67,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's that letter \Nthat arrived one week ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.51,0:10:27.31,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This song...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.60,0:10:28.68,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The "Moonlight Sonata!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:29.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.86,0:10:30.56,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.97,0:10:39.39,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! We were too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.52,0:10:48.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.99,0:10:50.49,DCMain,MOB B,0000,0000,0000,,Kawashima-san is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.49,0:10:51.88,DCMain,MOB C,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:54.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, call the police substation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.09,0:10:54.87,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.35,0:10:58.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else, stay where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.00,0:11:00.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Narumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.15,0:11:01.26,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.50,0:11:03.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you examine the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.77,0:11:04.97,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.89,0:11:12.32,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:16.15,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is what that letter \Nwas warning us about.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.15,0:11:19.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! If only I'd realized \Nwhat it meant sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.33,0:11:21.96,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.78,0:11:25.04,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the piano's curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.04,0:11:26.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.25,0:11:28.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.40,0:11:33.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a curse or a ghost \Nthat's playing the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.68,0:11:35.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's this tape recorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.59,0:11:46.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this is a murder case made \Nto look like the previous two incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.38,0:11:51.64,DCMain,MURASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on. Don't go making up stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.92,0:11:54.46,DCMain,MURASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.88,0:11:58.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Me? I came here from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.37,0:12:02.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the great detective Mori Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.52,0:12:05.38,DCMain,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,Ever heard of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.38,0:12:06.40,DCMain,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.09,0:12:12.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seawater?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.83,0:12:20.81,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the body's condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.81,0:12:25.43,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,the estimated time of death is \N30 minutes to one hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.43,0:12:27.69,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of death is suffocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.69,0:12:30.80,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I believe he was drowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.80,0:12:33.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was drowned?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.40,0:12:36.91,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say for certain without \Nperforming an autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.91,0:12:39.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think Doctor Narumi is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.05,0:12:42.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look outside the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.01,0:12:45.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that Kawashima-san's jacket?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:50.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like something was dragged from the \Ndoor leading out to the sea to the piano,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.55,0:12:53.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and there's mud and sand \Non Kawashima-san's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:13:00.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Also, the room's doors \Nand windows are locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.34,0:13:05.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the first few minutes of this \N"Moonlight Sonata" tape are blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.28,0:13:11.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,During the service, the culprit probably brought\N Kawashima-san to the ocean and drowned him,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.74,0:13:14.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,moved the body into this room, \Nlocked the doors and windows,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.67,0:13:17.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,turned on the tape recorder, \Nand then left the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.51,0:13:24.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After several minutes of silence, the "Moonlight \NSonata" started playing on the tape recorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.90,0:13:26.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.56,0:13:28.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:36.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But since we were in the entryway of \Nthe community center the whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.24,0:13:40.18,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute. Does that mean \Nthe culprit is still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.15,0:13:43.38,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.91,0:13:49.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, as long as they didn't \Nuse the confusion to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.42,0:13:50.94,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mister Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.20,0:13:57.09,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't call it a motive, but the \Nman happiest about Kawashima's death
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.09,0:14:02.81,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,is probably the other mayoral \Ncandidate, Shimizu-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.81,0:14:04.28,DCMain,SHIMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,W-What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.28,0:14:07.58,DCMain,SHIMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,I could say the same thing \Nabout you, Mayor Kuroiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:08.57,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.57,0:14:10.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. Try to calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.49,0:14:15.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, how long as \Nthat piano been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.24,0:14:20.94,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,It was given to the community center \Nas a gift from Aso-san 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.94,0:14:23.13,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,It's been here ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.13,0:14:24.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,From Aso-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.81,0:14:29.60,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Aso-san's name is even on the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.57,0:14:32.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.51,0:14:34.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheet music?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.76,0:14:42.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd. This wasn't here when \Nwe looked at it this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.31,0:14:48.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.31,0:14:50.43,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto Ken-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:51.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.77,0:14:55.36,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,He was quite prosperous a long time ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.36,0:14:58.42,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,but after the previous mayor \Npassed away two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.42,0:15:01.05,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,he began shutting himself inside his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.50,0:15:04.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Since the incident two years ago, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.09,0:15:09.55,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. I believe that Mayor Kuroiwa \Nand he are childhood friends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.82,0:15:12.54,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.99,0:15:15.19,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.27,0:15:19.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a police officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.37,0:15:21.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Took you long enough, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.33,0:15:23.10,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.10,0:15:26.60,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, who called for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.60,0:15:29.71,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,This man. His name is Mori Kogoro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.56,0:15:33.26,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.31,0:15:37.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, it's already late.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.57,0:15:40.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We'll interview the witnesses tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.61,0:15:47.46,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. This case is full of unknowns.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.20,0:15:52.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the culprit bother to \Nmove the body to the piano?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.14,0:15:57.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Does this sheet music that was found \Nwith the body mean anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.02,0:16:02.48,DCNote,NOTE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(145,1)\an8\b1\fs30\3c&HACB6BD&\c&H31373A&}the shadows will begin to vanish
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.22,0:16:01.97,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And what about the letter \Nwarning us about this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.45,0:16:04.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.60,0:16:08.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think that letter said "begin to vanish."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.45,0:16:11.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that this case is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.10,0:16:13.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:17.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This letter warned us about this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.50,0:16:22.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. "The shadows will vanish" means \Nthey'll be enveloped in light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.78,0:16:25.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That light is the moon's light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.43,0:16:26.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's referring to the "Moonlight Sonata."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.93,0:16:30.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. Both 12 years \Nago and two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:35.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the "Moonlight Sonata" was playing right \Nup until Aso-san and Kameyama-san died.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.78,0:16:39.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if the \Nshadows will vanish again,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.05,0:16:43.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,that means the "Moonlight Sonata" will be \Nplayed again, and somebody else will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.43,0:16:44.89,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.25,0:16:48.41,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,This letter says that the shadows \Nwill "begin to vanish."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.59,0:16:53.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean there's more to this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.22,0:16:58.30,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.61,0:17:05.15,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,If you ask me, spending the night \Nhere with the body is insanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:07.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.68,0:17:11.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, who moved the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.67,0:17:13.59,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,That was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.59,0:17:17.75,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I felt bad about leaving \Nhim in that position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.75,0:17:19.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.50,0:17:21.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The crime scene hasn't been \Nproperly examined yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.77,0:17:22.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:25.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That sheet music is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.55,0:17:26.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.81,0:17:31.45,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I thought I'd hold \Nonto it for safekeeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.45,0:17:32.28,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:36.63,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This is the sheet music \Nfor the "Moonlight Sonata."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.63,0:17:37.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The "Moonlight Sonata"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.41,0:17:43.15,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the fourth line is sort of weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.15,0:17:44.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The fourth line?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.03,0:17:46.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Weird how?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.65,0:17:48.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.78,0:17:50.99,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,When you play the fourth line...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.18,0:17:56.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.94,0:18:03.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could the fourth line of this sheet music \Nbe a dying message from Kawashima-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.00,0:18:08.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's possible that the \Nculprit will return to retrieve this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.00,0:18:13.82,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Narumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.82,0:18:17.86,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I called your inn, and \Nthey said you'd be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.86,0:18:20.33,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I brought you dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.33,0:18:22.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,N-Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.44,0:18:26.57,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.83,0:18:30.53,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,So you're not originally from \Nthis island, Doctor Narumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.53,0:18:34.33,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No. I go back to Tokyo every weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.61,0:18:37.58,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's been two years since \NI started coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.58,0:18:39.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.28,0:18:41.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I have a question about Mayor \NKameyama who died two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.23,0:18:48.20,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He'd previously had heart problems, and \Nthe cause of death was a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.58,0:18:51.86,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But his face was rather tense,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.42,0:18:55.61,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,as though he'd seen something terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.98,0:18:59.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He looked like he'd seen \Nsomething terrifying, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.41,0:19:06.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I'll keep watch tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.61,0:19:08.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You guys should go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.59,0:19:09.81,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.55,0:19:16.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mori-kun. Mori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.54,0:19:19.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's afternoon already. Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.05,0:19:23.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I-Inspector Megure, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.38,0:19:26.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you're not still asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.86,0:19:32.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you were involved, \Nso I came all the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.01,0:19:33.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.48,0:19:36.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, I have something for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.10,0:19:38.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun already gave me the sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.79,0:19:39.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.81,0:19:44.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The three of them outlined \Nthe case for me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:48.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,All three of them were awake \Nby the time we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.71,0:19:49.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.21,0:19:55.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, we're interviewing \Npeople at the village office.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.10,0:19:56.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Come lend us a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.53,0:19:58.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.07,0:20:09.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Did you figured out who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.36,0:20:10.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.84,0:20:13.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We've got 38 witnesses to question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.93,0:20:16.85,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,When will I be questioned?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.85,0:20:18.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you're exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:20.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I asked them to question you last.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.46,0:20:24.00,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll go wash my face first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.35,0:20:25.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.12,0:20:29.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How many more people do \Nyou have to question?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.33,0:20:34.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Six total. There's Doctor \NNarumi, those four over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.34,0:20:37.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and Nishimoto, who's being \Nquestioned right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.01,0:20:39.95,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.22,0:20:42.34,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Cursed piano, my ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.34,0:20:45.57,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,This happened because that \Nthing is still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.57,0:20:47.18,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.41,0:20:50.04,DCMain,TATSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Get rid of it immediately. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.84,0:20:53.00,DCMain,HIRATA,0000,0000,0000,,V-Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.21,0:21:00.47,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.47,0:21:04.48,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I obviously don't have a motive \Nto kill Kawashima-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.48,0:21:09.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I told you, we're just questioning everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.78,0:21:09.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow. Reiko-san has been \Nyelling for ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.24,0:21:10.35,DCMain,REIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.84,0:21:10.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.86,0:21:12.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now, now. Please calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.53,0:21:14.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They've been interviewed already, \Nso why aren't they leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.73,0:21:18.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:21.45,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.28,0:21:24.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did Nishimoto-san go in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.50,0:21:26.79,DCMain,MURASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No. Only Shimizu is inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.09,0:21:28.70,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. He must be upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.89,0:21:30.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.42,0:21:32.86,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,This song...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.29,0:21:36.17,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the second movement \Nof the "Moonlight Sonata."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.17,0:21:38.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the source of the sound?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.01,0:21:40.89,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The broadcast room?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.96,0:21:43.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nishimoto-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.95,0:21:48.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mayor Kuroiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.59,0:21:51.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Call forensics and the coroner immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.13,0:21:56.13,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,But Inspector, the coroner left for \NTokyo to perform Kawashima's autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.13,0:21:58.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. Why did this have to happen now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.59,0:21:59.42,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.49,0:22:02.46,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't mind, I could do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.46,0:22:03.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Narumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.19,0:22:05.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.92,0:22:08.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, until the forensics team \Narrives, could you examine him right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.79,0:22:09.56,DCMain,NARUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.76,0:22:14.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Again. I knew it was coming, \Nbut I let another person die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.97,0:22:16.48,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.48,0:22:20.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Threatening to commit murder and then \Ncalmly carrying out that threat...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.11,0:22:24.47,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They won't get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.97,0:23:47.61,DCMain,SHIMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The hellfire's grudge? Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HC9CBCC&\3c&HA4AAB3&}Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.61,0:23:48.75,DCMain,NISHIMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,It's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.00,0:23:51.45,DCMain,NISHIMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Aso Keiji is alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.57,0:23:57.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Murasawa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.88,0:24:01.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nishimoto-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.03,0:24:06.99,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Moonlight Sonata Murder \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.46,0:24:14.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NMoonlight Sonata Murder, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:34.95,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Piano
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.49,0:24:33.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.18,0:24:34.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:36.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Cock-a-doodle-doo!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:39.94,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.12,0:24:37.10,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}After that moonlit night...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.10,0:24:38.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}...we'll probably see blue skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.91,0:24:39.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Nice!
